§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $f: D → 𝗥$ be a multivariate real-valued function where
    $D ⊂ 𝗥^d$. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬graph❭ of $f$ is the set in $𝗥^{d + 1}$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set{(x, f(x)) ∈ 𝗥^d × 𝗥}{x ∈ D}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ The ❬epigraph❭ of $f$ is the set in $𝗥^{d + 1}$ defined
    by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \Set{(x, t) ∈ 𝗥^{d}}{x ∈ D \text{ and } f(x) ≤ t}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the epigraph of a function $f$ by $\epi f$. ⦉
⦉

