§§ Connecting convex sets and convex functions ⦉

‖ A function $f: 𝗥^d → 𝗥$ is convex if and only if $\epi f$
  is a convex set. ⦉

§§ Note on terminology ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The prefix “epi” is Greek, meaning “above”. ⦉
⦉

